The operating system command used to check out files from the Version Control System before files are exported to the file system by the repository export or flush procedures.
E.g. tf.exe checkout <file>
VCSs such as SVN do not require check-out operations in order to update a file in the file system. TFS generally leaves files read-only unless they have first been checked out.
